servings: 2
---

Boil a full #kettle{}. Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (peel first if
you prefer).

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{0.5%tsp}.

Once boiling, add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip a
knife through, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small
pieces).

While the potatoes cook, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{}
on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @unconventional plant-based burgers{2} and onion. Use a
#spoon{} to mash into a mince-like texture as it cooks. Cook until browned,
~{5-6%minutes}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Ensure they're piping hot throughout.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once the mince is browned, add the garlic and @Central American style spice
mix{1%sachet}. Stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @red wine stock paste{28%grams},
@Worcester sauce{15%grams}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{75%ml} for the sauce (see
pantry for both amounts).

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, until
thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off
the heat.

Add the @butter{20%grams} and a splash of @?milk{} and mash with a #potato
masher{} until smooth.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

Once the tomato sauce has thickened, stir through the @peas{120%grams}.

Cook until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir half the @hard Italian style cheese{20%grams}(grated) into the sauce. Taste
and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed, then remove from the heat.

When everything's ready, serve the spiced veggie mince ragu alongside the buttery
mash.

Finish by sprinkling over the remaining cheese.

Enjoy!